discussion.content:
Since you want to have "name" and "email" as labels for the intended release you need to create an annotated tag.

From [Git SCM book](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Basics-Tagging):
Annotated tags, however, are stored as full objects in the Git database. They’re checksummed; contain the tagger name, email, and date; have a tagging message;
